// Annotation Utilities
// Helper functions for working with HTML comment-style annotation markers embedded in markdown.
// Supports stripping markers for clean export and counting annotations by type.

FUNCTION stripAnnotationMarkers(content) -> string                      EXPORT
  Remove all annotation comment patterns from the content:
    comment blocks, comment-start/end pairs, status markers (proposed/approved/rejected),
    propose-start/end, approve-start/end, and reject-start/end patterns.
  Collapse runs of 3+ blank lines down to 2.
  Return the trimmed result.

---

FUNCTION countAnnotations(content) -> { comment, propose, approve, reject }  EXPORT
  Count occurrences of each annotation type using regex matching.
  Returns an object with integer counts for comment, propose, approve, and reject.

---

FUNCTION downloadCleanMarkdown(filename, content)                       EXPORT
  CALLS: stripAnnotationMarkers (annotationUtils)
  Strip annotation markers from content.
  Create a Blob and trigger a browser file download.
  Output filename is the original filename (without .md) suffixed with '-clean.md'.
